It was during a sort of deep talk at lunch with my teammates, that I had a deep discussion with Hadi about the future. I talked about the goals I wanted to reach, all the things I wanted to learn, but how far away or out of reach they seemed. He then told me something like
&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s see in seven years where are you at&rdquo;
It was something like a challenge and at the same time a promise, an expectation, a motivation.

‘Motivation may get you to take on a task or behavior that you don’t normally do but eventually that motivation will either not be there any more or won’t be effective.’
&lsquo;I think many of us have a will to overcome existing habits and form new ones but we lack the way to do so. Too many distractions, too many opportunities, too many excuses.&rsquo;
